<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFB57458FF07FEDEFED5FE77" blockId="11.[151,699,333,395]" box="[151,359,369,395]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Bicolored Antpitta</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="86EC6543FFB57458FF07FE16FC55FE2F" box="[151,999,441,467]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFB57458FF07FE16FC55FE2F" blockId="11.[151,1437,441,1008]" box="[151,999,441,467]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Includes populations designated 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FD95FE16FD35FE2F" authorityName="Sclater &amp; Salvin" authorityYear="1879" box="[517,647,441,467]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufocinerea">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FD95FE16FD35FE2F" box="[517,647,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">rufocinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FD2DFE15FC85FE2F" box="[701,823,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">romeroana</emphasis>
in the analysis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="86EC6543FFB57458FF57FE72FB22FD50" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFB57458FF57FE72FB22FD50" blockId="11.[151,1437,441,1008]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FF57FE72FEF0FE0B" bold="true" box="[199,322,477,503]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Differs from all other species in the complex in having gray underparts that contrast sharply with its rufous head, throat, and upperparts. Its long song (
<figureCitation id="56CD2A4DFFB57458FD51FDAEFCB1FDE0" box="[705,771,513,540]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,1033,1750]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,1029,1756]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 5. Songs of Grallaria rufocinerea: (A) long song, RN Río Blanco, Caldas, Colombia (van Oosten XC18278); (B) short song, RN Río Blanco (Geale XC51230)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3954709" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3954709/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), a nearly evenly paced series of similar notes, distinguishes 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FF07FD8AFE89FDC3" authorityName="Sclater &amp; Salvin" authorityYear="1879" box="[151,315,549,575]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufocinerea">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FF07FD8AFE89FDC3" box="[151,315,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. rufocinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other taxa in the complex, except 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FC8DFD8AFBAAFDC3" box="[797,1048,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FC8DFD8AFC31FDC3" baseAuthorityName="Lafresnaye" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[797,899,549,575]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufula">G. rufula</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E7B157A1FFB57458FC1BFD89FBAAFDC3" box="[907,1048,550,575]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
. Its single-noted short song distinguishes 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FF61FDE6FE27FD9F" authorityName="Sclater &amp; Salvin" authorityYear="1879" box="[241,405,585,611]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufocinerea">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FF61FDE6FE27FD9F" box="[241,405,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. rufocinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FE47FDE6FD7DFD9F" box="[471,719,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FE47FDE6FD8EFD9F" baseAuthorityName="Lafresnaye" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[471,572,585,611]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufula">G. rufula</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E7B157A1FFB57458FDD3FDE5FD7DFD9F" box="[579,719,586,611]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and from all other taxa except 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FBB6FDE6FB1BFD9F" authorityName="Hosner, Robbins, Isler, &amp; Chesser" authorityYear="2020" box="[1062,1193,585,611]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centralis">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FBB6FDE6FB1BFD9F" box="[1062,1193,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. centralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FB4EFDE6FA26FD9F" authorityName="Hosner, Robbins, Isler, &amp; Chesser" authorityYear="2020" box="[1246,1428,585,611]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ayacuchensis">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FB4EFDE6FA26FD9F" box="[1246,1428,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. ayacuchensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; it is distinguished from the latter two species by greater duration and by note shape, which is flat or very slightly upslurred, as contrasted with 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FE70FD3EFDD6FD57" authorityName="Hosner, Robbins, Isler, &amp; Chesser" authorityYear="2020" box="[480,612,657,683]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centralis">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FE70FD3EFDD6FD57" box="[480,612,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. centralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(inverted U) and 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FCBBFD3EFC51FD57" authorityName="Hosner, Robbins, Isler, &amp; Chesser" authorityYear="2020" box="[811,995,657,683]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ayacuchensis">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FCBBFD3EFC51FD57" box="[811,995,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. ayacuchensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(downslurred).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="86EC6543FFB57458FF57FD1AFD96FCC7" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFB57458FF57FD1AFBA8FD08" blockId="11.[151,1437,441,1008]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FF57FD1AFED3FD33" bold="true" box="[199,353,693,719]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Distribution.</emphasis>
Central Andes from central 
<collectingRegion id="0C32F82AFFB57458FD09FD1AFCBEFD33" box="[665,780,693,719]" country="Colombia" name="Antioquia" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Antioquia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="B6E17658FFB57458FC86FD1AFC35FD33" box="[790,903,693,719]" name="Colombia" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, south to the upper 
<collectingRegion id="0C32F82AFFB57458FBCFFD1AFB69FD33" box="[1119,1243,693,719]" country="Colombia" name="Magdalena" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Magdalena</collectingRegion>
Valley and along the eastern slope from 
<collectingRegion id="0C32F82AFFB57458FE06FD76FE6DFD0F" box="[406,479,729,755]" country="Colombia" name="Cauca" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Cauca</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="B6E17658FFB57458FE7AFD76FDE9FD0F" box="[490,603,729,755]" name="Colombia" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, to 
<collectingRegion id="0C32F82AFFB57458FD13FD76FCB0FD0F" box="[643,770,729,755]" country="Ecuador" name="Sucumbios" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Sucumbíos</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="B6E17658FFB57458FC9EFD76FCDFFD0F" box="[782,877,729,755]" name="Ecuador" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<quantity id="090E9B2DFFB57458FCE8FD76FBA4FD08" box="[888,1046,729,756]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="3.25" metricValueMin="1.95" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="2600.0" valueMax="3250.0" valueMin="1950.0">1950–3250 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFB57458FF57FD52FD96FCC7" blockId="11.[151,1437,441,1008]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FF57FD52FE85FCEB" bold="true" box="[199,311,765,791]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Plumage.</emphasis>
The dark gray underparts of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FD17FD52FC9EFCEB" authorityName="Sclater &amp; Salvin" authorityYear="1879" box="[647,812,765,791]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufocinerea">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FD17FD52FC9EFCEB" box="[647,812,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. rufocinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unique in the 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FC6EFD52FBD7FCEB" baseAuthorityName="Lafresnaye" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[1022,1125,765,791]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufula">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FC6EFD52FBD7FCEB" box="[1022,1125,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. rufula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex (specimen photographs App. 6, 
<figureCitation id="56CD2A4DFFB57458FED2FC8EFE1CFCC7" box="[322,430,801,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1975,1999]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,1607,1947]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1435,1605,1950]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 17. Songs of Grallaria sinaensis: (A) long song, Río Keara, PN Madidi, La Paz, Bolivia (Tobias XC73603); (B) short song, Río Keara, PN Madidi (Tobias XC73602)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3954733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3954733/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs. A17</figureCitation>
and A 
<figureCitation id="56CD2A4DFFB57458FE6BFC8EFDA5FCC7" box="[507,535,801,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,1500,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[152,1436,1497,1847]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 18. Songs of Grallaria cochabambae: (A) long song, Chuspipata, La Paz, Bolivia (Rowlett ML236894); (B) short song, Corioco Road, La Paz (Boesman XC223701)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3954735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3954735/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="86EC6543FFB57458FF57FCEAFE54F81A" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFB57458FF57FCEAFB98FC0C" blockId="11.[151,1437,441,1008]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FF57FCEAFE89FCA3" bold="true" box="[199,315,837,863]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</emphasis>
Species status is supported by vocal as well as plumage characters. Reexamination of the taxonomic status of 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FE91FCC5FEC9FC7F" box="[257,379,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">romeroana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AA674B39FFB57458FE1DFCC6FD5DFC7F" author="Hernandez C. &amp; J. I &amp; Rodriguez M." box="[397,751,873,899]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="573 - 580" refId="ref22255" refString="Hernandez C., J. I. &amp; Rodriguez M., J. V. (1979) Dos nuevos taxa del genero Grallaria (Aves: Formicariidae) del alto valle del Magdalena (Colombia). Caldasia, 12, 573 - 580." type="journal article" year="1979">Hernández &amp; Rodríguez, 1979</bibRefCitation>
) requires more vocal data, especially recordings of its long song, as well as additional plumage comparisons with the nominate. Pending that review, we recommend its maintenance as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FE52FC1EFDF6FC37" authorityName="Sclater &amp; Salvin" authorityYear="1879" box="[450,580,945,971]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufocinerea">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FE52FC1EFDF6FC37" box="[450,580,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">rufocinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the original description. The geographic range of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FB4FFC1EFA31FC37" authorityName="Sclater &amp; Salvin" authorityYear="1879" box="[1247,1411,945,971]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufocinerea">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FB4FFC1EFA31FC37" box="[1247,1411,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. rufocinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sympatric/parapatric with that of northern populations of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFB57458FC8AFC7AFC2BFC13" authorityName="Domaniewski &amp; Stolzmann" authorityYear="1918" box="[794,921,981,1007]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saturata">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFB57458FC8AFC7AFC2BFC13" box="[794,921,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">G. saturata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below).
</paragraph>
